==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gorgonian
<hw>Gor*go"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Gorgoneus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or
resembling, a Gorgon; terrifying into stone; terrific.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rest his look⟦br⟧
Bound with <qex>Gorgonian</qex> rigor not to move.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to the Gorgoniacea;
<as>as, <ex>gorgonian</ex> coral</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gorgonian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gorgonian
<hw>Gor*go"ni*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the
Gorgoniacea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gorgonize</ent>⟦br⟧
